
--- DIRECTIVES ----

IMPORT

Brings Module's functions & macros into current scope.

Syntax:
import Module [, only:|except: ]



ALIAS

alias My.Other.Module.Parser, as: Parser
||
alias My.Other.Module.Parser
||
alias My.Other.Module.{Parser, Runner}

Reduce typing by using alias


REQUIRE

Brings Module's macros



--- ATTRIBUTES ---

They are metadata, associated with a module

defmodule MyModule do
    @my_attr "blah"
end